'''Easter term''' is the summer term at the [[University of Cambridge]], the [[University of Wales, Lampeter]], [[University of Durham]], and formerly [[University of Newcastle upon Tyne]] (before 2004<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070521020836/http://www.ncl.ac.uk/press.office/newslink/?ref=1077708461 University terms to be renamed], [[University of Newcastle upon Tyne]], UK, 25 February 2004.</ref>), in the [[United Kingdom]]. It runs from April to June.
The expression is also used for the third term of the [[legal year]] in the [[Courts of England and Wales]], many schools and other educational institutions.
