The '''International Cultural Research Center''' is a [[Turkey (country)|Turkish]] [[think tank]] based in [[Istanbul, Turkey]]. It is generally known by its short name in Turkish, UKAM. Founded in 2012, UKAM conducts research and provides [[education]] in [[ethnic studies|ethnic]] and [[cultural studies]]. It focuses on [[minority group|minority]] issues, particularly those of the [[Kurds]] and other non-[[Muslim]] groups in Turkey, in an attempt to strengthen Turkish [[democracy]] and foster [[ethnic diversity|ethnic]] and [[cultural diversity]].<ref>http://www.ukam.org/</ref>

